this will remove your data or may cause your phone to brick
proceed with care
steps:
1) turn on developer options
2) developer options > enable usb debugging 
3) plug in device to pc 
4) install USB drivers for your phone, refer: https://developer.android.com/studio/run/oem-usb
5) download and install adb, refer:  https://forum.xda-developers.com/t/tool-minimal-adb-and-fastboot-2-9-18.2317790/
6) open a terminal in the installation folder
string in [] are the commands to type in the terminal
7) [adb devices] - to verify device is detected
8) [adb shell] - to login in to device's shell
9) [pm list packages] - to check what package are available 
10) copy the list below into the terminal to remove all useless packages 



